<p>With a basic design and a range of versatile uses, the dumbbell helps to build the foundational basics. It keeps things simple by using a handle and a dumbbell weight head attached to either end.&nbsp;</p>



<p>Adjustable dumbbells are a dumbbell variation that combines several dumbbell weights into one equipment piece. They offer an adjustable weight, allowing you to perform a range of <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/dumbbell-exercises" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">dumbbell exercises </a>without heading to the weight rack. Alongside this, they’re space-saving and cost-efficient.&nbsp;</p>



<p>To help you choose something suitable, we’ve reviewed our top ten best adjustable dumbbells below.</p>



