<p>Let&#8217;s start with the construction, as it&#8217;s one of their best features. We can see that they use a combination of steel and chrome. This gives you great durability with some added protection using a sleek finish.</p>



<p>In terms of weight range, they go from 5–80 pounds. This gives you a great amount of options to choose from as a beginner or advanced athlete.&nbsp;</p>



<p>You can use them for compound movements, smaller isolation-type exercises, and anything in between. These are also known as <a href="https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC4592763/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">multi-joint or single-joint movements</a>.</p>



<p>However, they do use bigger 5-pound weight increments, which is something that can be worked on. Future models could offer smaller weight increments at the lower end of the weight range.&nbsp;</p>



<p>To adjust them, simply twist the handles and select your weight. We’re surprised they can use this with such a high weight range. However, this is a testament to their innovative design.&nbsp;</p>



<p><strong>Overall, these dumbbells do everything really well. If you’re happy to pay the higher price tag, these should last for a lifetime. You definitely won’t regret purchasing a pair once you start using them!</strong></p>



